in a classroom with children that were disrespecting the teacher, even cussing at the teacher without any recourse, the level of learning dropped dramatically and the child became depressed and her learning suffered.  So it really is not that simple as good parents just sending their kids to public school and changing it that way.  Unfortunately not all public schools are equally bad.  On the other hand, in the district I live in the public schools I feel are just as good, if not better then the private schools. There are many layers to the issue here. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="856" language="en" documentId="4035" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Mar99868" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:57PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="6" thumbsDown="0" origId="4035" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="856"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>